Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.23,0:00:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Men are transient.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.52,0:00:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time is hollow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.11,0:00:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea is volatile.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.87,0:00:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Headed for the same port, we travel across the shifting waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.53,0:00:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange things occur, and we suspect one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.58,0:00:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayakashi, Mononoke, Umi Bozu.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.33,0:00:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as darkness exists within the\Nhearts of men, there will always be more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.68,0:00:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let them come, for my invitation is what they fear most.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.46,0:01:08.79,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The blue moon illuminated
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.83,0:01:12.76,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}your wandering shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:17.26,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I could never tell you all I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.26,0:01:22.18,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,250)}It was so very frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.27,0:01:26.06,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I think about your faked smile,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.64,0:01:30.69,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}and forget all the hot tears we shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.15,0:01:33.36,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}What do these empty husks,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.40,0:01:39.20,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}those empty eyes of yours, reflect, my dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.95,0:01:44.41,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The transient quarter moon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.79,0:01:46.58,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,100)}hides in a rift in the clouds,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.54,0:01:48.96,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(100,300)}as darkness seeps up from the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:53.42,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Tell me the truth, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.75,0:01:55.59,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Are you so despondent
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.67,0:01:59.97,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,0)}that you still sit alone, sighing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:01.97,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}The Second Act
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.57,0:02:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Medicine Seller did indeed\Nexorcise the Ghost Cat from the Sakai mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Sakai family were all killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.74,0:02:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who did he save, in the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.50,0:02:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose side is he on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.92,0:02:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With a face like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it will be a wonder if you ever marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.17,0:02:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that you’d tell me the truth, but let me ask anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn’t change the compass’s\Nheading, did you, Mr. Medicine Seller?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I did not tamper with the compass,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.48,0:02:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the fact remains that I have been taken to\Nthe Dragon’s Triangle, the Ayakashi’s Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that sword alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.46,0:03:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.83,0:03:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Mr. Medicine Seller, I\Nunderstand that you’re a powerful man,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but don’t you think that aloof\Nattitude of yours is a little over the top?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of thing does nothing to impress us girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said before that Ayakashi\Nand Mononoke are different, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.40,0:03:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren’t they pretty much the same, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.69,0:03:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you said, the Ayakashi are similar to Gods\Nin that there are countless numbers of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as there are men and beasts and birds in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are many types of Ayakashi,\Nwhich exist outside of our plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.20,0:03:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are Ayakashi the ghosts of dead people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In some cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ghost ship we fought off was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:04:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, since tools and objects have souls\Nas well, their variations are multifarious indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how they came to be, though, an\NAyakashi’s reason for being is beyond human understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what about Mononoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the “ke” in Mononoke refers to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I knew, would I be asking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.69,0:04:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means “disease.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the “mono” refers to their godly nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Mononoke haunt people like a disease?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.86,0:04:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vengeance, sadness, fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would happen if an Ayakashi\Nwere to unite with a strong human emotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would become incredibly\Npowerful, unhindered by attempts to seal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your Sword of Exorcism could still kill it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But without the Mononoke’s…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Form, Truth and Regret, you cannot draw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by “truth” and “regret”?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth is the state of the object.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.35,0:04:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regret is the state of the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, the state of things, is it…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.48,0:05:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, are there Mononoke here, as well as Ayakashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Egad, those monks are positively useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.76,0:05:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be it Ayakashi or Mononoke, I will vanquish this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.60,0:05:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.77,0:05:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.53,0:05:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This could be problematic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.87,0:06:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So many Onibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s nice to have some light, but it’s still awfully creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s something coming from the bow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:17.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s an Ayakashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.89,0:06:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I should be able to cut it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.69,0:06:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it’s an Ayakashi! It’s flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s an Umizatou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won’t be able to kill it with a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.32,0:06:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.87,0:06:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will ask if it is frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not answer that it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell it that it is not frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then will it leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.13,0:06:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um, wait…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.72,0:06:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that’s right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“I don’t know what lies at the end of this journey.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.64,0:07:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell it that is what you fear most.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Denizens of this ship, answer me this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.99,0:07:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.07,0:07:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will question you one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.70,0:07:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Refuse to answer, and you will be\Nforced to wander the sea as the living dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, ask away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y—Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.34,0:07:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.51,0:07:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th—That I d—d—don’t know what lies at the e—end of—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.23,0:07:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you truly fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, it’s that I’ll lose all my\Nm—m—money, and I’ll become a penniless beggar!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:54.82,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}W—Wait…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.10,0:08:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, my precious goldfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I built an aquarium in the ship to carry them all this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.20,0:08:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you fear most?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fear nothing in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.67,0:08:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I inherited this sword, I have\Nspilled the blood of a hundred men.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s nothing but a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.63,0:08:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve always wanted to kill an Ayakashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.60,0:08:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.91,0:09:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sasaki Hyouei,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.62,0:09:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how dare you kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.29,0:09:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouei-san…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re all dead! You’re dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.84,0:09:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You killed us all, Sasaki Hyouei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.39,0:09:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me be!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.43,0:09:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.64,0:09:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—It was my sword! I just want to get to Edo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Samurai!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that means he was\Nlying when he said he feared nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must always have been afraid of those he killed in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.68,0:10:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you go crazy if you lie to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you become like them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.35,0:10:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from their expressions,\Nyou’re shown all your worst fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.27,0:10:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it’s the same whether you lie or tell the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.11,0:10:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the problem lies within you, no-one else can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s so weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.75,0:10:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.38,0:10:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you fear most?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:11:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O—Oh dear, right now I fear {\i1}you{\i0} the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder, though. What do I really fear most?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.97,0:11:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.56,0:11:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D—Don’t rush me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I’ve never really been in love, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.31,0:11:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have so many wonderful experiences ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll marry a wonderful guy, and have a bunch of cute children…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.82,0:11:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I suppose what I fear most is that I’ll\Ndie without ever having done any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.33,0:12:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N—No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t want to get married! I\Ndon’t want to have a baby like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.29,0:12:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.54,0:12:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the Umizatou shows you is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.59,0:12:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is merely a bad dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your true self does not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.13,0:12:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Medicine Seller…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I’m next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.14,0:12:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you fear most?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.19,0:12:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—I…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.02,0:12:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I fear most is…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P—P—Pastries!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.94,0:12:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m afraid of pastries.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.36,0:12:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s just lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.00,0:12:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.88,0:13:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s so plump and delici—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what he’s seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I don’t want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.15,0:13:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, of the three of us, who\Nwill have to answer the Umizatou next?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask me. I will answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.12,0:13:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you fear most?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.95,0:13:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I fear most is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.58,0:13:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the knowledge that the edge of this\Nworld exists without Form, Truth or Regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.88,0:14:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Medicine Seller?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mononoke’s Sea, where the Ayakashi roam…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was this ship sent to this sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—I…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.36,0:14:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you truly fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.82,0:14:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—What I truly fear is…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.49,0:14:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I truly fear is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.16,0:14:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.41,0:14:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.87,0:15:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama is a wonderful master,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.54,0:15:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but so many unusual things have happened on this trip to Edo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.76,0:15:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.30,0:15:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were chanting all night, but then…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.77,0:15:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sougen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.19,0:15:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y—Yes, Genkei-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.73,0:15:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you feeling seasick, after this long journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.07,0:15:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.57,0:15:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you are, then go get some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.78,0:15:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.33,0:15:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had failed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.67,0:15:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My master was the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who could have placed the magnet near the compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did not want to involve you all,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but no ship dared take me to the\NDragon’s Triangle, no matter how I pleaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.55,0:16:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you want to come here\Nso badly, though it terrifies you so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.43,0:16:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umizatou, ask your question!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.78,0:16:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s been waiting for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.61,0:17:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For fifty years, I have trembled\Nin fear every time I’ve thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is within this sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.79,0:17:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has wandered this sea constantly, and even\Nchanged it, that the Ayakashi might swarm to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.85,0:17:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What made the Ayakashi’s Sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.03,0:17:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Utsurobune on which my sister sailed, fifty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Umizatou gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.27,0:18:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s an Utsurobune?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.94,0:18:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it’s a sort of ship made by hollowing out a large tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.23,0:18:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the hull is a cave?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get on a ship like that, you’ll never be able to get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.78,0:18:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. You couldn’t get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.37,0:18:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s the kind of ship it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-san, why would your sister get on a ship like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of chains!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chains that bound the Utsurobune!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.63,0:19:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that an illusion, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s the Utsurobune!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not an illusion! I can see it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.01,0:19:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama, what happened fifty years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did your sister get into that Utsurobune?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.60,0:19:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can such a small ship make such huge waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.58,0:19:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.62,0:19:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s coming from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s a person!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s someone in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:19:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She’s been in there for fifty years? That’s impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t take it! I can’t… I can’t stand such fear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.97,0:20:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are this Mononoke’s{\alpha&HFF&} Truth and Regret?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.77,0:20:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are this Mononoke’s Truth and{\alpha&HFF&} Regret?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.43,0:20:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are this Mononoke’s Truth and Regret?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.86,0:20:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Oyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have not forgotten you even once in the last fifty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You went into the Utsurobune in my place of your own accord,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.00,0:20:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and were taken to the Dragon’s Triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you harbor such hatred, that you\Ncould change the sea and draw all these Ayakashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.68,0:20:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.65,0:21:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mononoke’s Form
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.49,0:21:09.95,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}To be continued
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.70,0:21:19.21,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Without you, I just can’t smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.34,0:21:30.26,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I walk this banal town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.26,0:21:36.35,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}feeling such intense emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:42.73,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I know that if I could treasure them and live on,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.82,0:21:52.04,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I would need nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.70,0:22:00.21,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}The summer flowers that bloomed in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.21,0:22:06.51,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Come falling down, dancing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.59,0:22:09.84,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I can barely recall the night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.84,0:22:13.14,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}where they all came tumbling down,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.14,0:22:23.98,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}so what I can still recall is all the more precious.
